com.amitinside.featureflags

Interface Strategizable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Feature, FeatureGroup

    public interface Strategizable
    A class implements the Strategizable interface to indicate that the instances of the class can be used to provide strategic information for its enablement. Strategic information can be provided by implementing ActivationStrategy interface.
    See Also:
    Feature, FeatureGroup, ActivationStrategy

        boolean isEnabled()
        Checks whether the strategizable is enabled in its configuration. This only shows the configuration provided to the strategizable.
